copy.title: spiderStitching
copy.instruction0: When the spider is over the target, click to tell her to make a stitch.
copy.instruction1: Be careful - you only have a single chance!
copy.instruction2: Click when she's over the center of the target to earn more points.
copy.title: Spider Stitching
copy.subtitle: Level
copy.bobbinEncouragePerfect: Your stitching is a thing of beauty!
Wow, I couldn't have done better myself!
copy.bobbinEncourageAlright: Oh yeah, you're really stitching now!
Good stitch! I think the spider likes ya!
Keep on stitching, keep on stitching!
copy.bobbinDiscourage: Oh snip! Ya missed that one!
Spiders sure are quick, aren't they?
copy.bobbinPoor: You gave it your best stitch. I bet you'll do loads better next time!
Not bad. Try stitching again, and really concentrate! You'll do better!
Keep up that spider stitching - I know ya can do better!
Don't give up. All it takes is a little practice, and you'll be stitching like a pro!
copy.bobbinGood: What a hem-tastic job! Have ya done spider stitching before?
Hey-oh! You do spider-ific stitching! I'm proud of ya!
Well, thread a needle, ya did some nifty stitching with that spider!
Hey, you're pretty good with spider stitching, ya know that?
copy.bobbinGreat: Hems and stitches, what great work! Ya sure you're not a sewing-talent?
Stitch my hem, you're a natural spider guider!
Tailor-tastic job! Ya know, ya remind me of a certain weaving-talent Fairy from Autumn Forest?
Well, knot my thread, that's what I call stitch-arific work!
copy.bobbinAwesome: Okay, I'm officially astounded. Your spider stitching talents are awesome!
Ya might be the best tailor I've ever seen! Will ya stitch me your autograph?
My wings are a'quiver! Your spider stitching skills are awesome!
Well, bust my buttons! You're a stitch-arific tailor!
copy.mendyEncouragePerfect: Wonderful! That was a perfect stitch!
copy.mendyEncourageAlright: Very good! Now hurry, do another one!
We have a gift for spider stitching!
Our creation is going to look fabulous!
We make quite a good team with that spider!
copy.mendyDiscourage: That's okay, we'll fix it later.
Don't worry about that stitch, my dear.
copy.mendyPoor: Not to worry, my dear. We'll stitch better next time.
Dear dear, we stitched our best, didn't we? Why not try again?
Let's not let our wings droop. We all stitch better with practice, my dear.
Spider stitching can be a real challenge. We will need to practice a bit more, won't we, my dear?
copy.mendyGood: Not bad spider stitching, my dear. Needs a bit of improvement here and there, but not bad at all.
Good job, my dear. And remember, we'll spider stitch even better with regular practice!
Mmm, we certainly have a knack for guiding spiders, don't we?
Lovely, lovely! We are certainly no beginner to spider stitching, are we?
copy.mendyGreat: Well, my dear, we certainly have quite a flair for fashionable spider stitching!
We're quite impressed! Fantastic stitch work!
Quite lovely work! We are reminded of a certain sewing-talent Fairy from Spring Valley!
We've been practicing, haven't we? Lovely stitching!
copy.mendyAwesome: Pins and needles, my dear, what amazing spider skills we have!
Thimbles and thread! This just goes to show that practice does make perfect!
Astounding, my dear! We couldn't have done better!
